   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>Letter, William J. Helsley in Chattanooga, Tenn. to Mary Helsley in Southington, Ohio, 1864 September 7</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>In this letter, dated September 7, 1864, William J. Helsley in Chattanooga, Tenn. writes to his wife, Mary Helsley, in Southington, Ohio, reporting that General Sherman has "about used up the Rebel Army." He also informs Mary that General John Morgan has been killed near Bulls Gap, Tenn. He speculates that the war will "soon be over."</mods:abstract>
